{"lemma":"فَوّارٌ","slug":"فَوّارٌ","root":"ف.#.ر","root_slug":"ف-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34802"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"effervescent; sparkling, fizzy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Characteristic adjective from the root ف و ر (f w r)."},"ipa":["/faw.waːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34802","headword_ar":"فَوَّارٌ","root":"fwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an intensive epithet from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAra","text_ar":"فَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Boiling much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: ―         -b2-  and Water, &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"welling forth abundantly; gushing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faw~aArN","text_ar":"فَوَّارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A smiting"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that inflicts a wound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that the blood flows"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundantly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"biDarobK yuxaf~itu faw~aAruhu\n                      \n                     \n                        waTaEonK taraY Ald~ama minohu ra$iy$FA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*aA qataluwA minokumu faArisFA\n                      \n                     \n                        Damin~aA lahu baEodahu A^ano yaEiy$aA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, TA. [The text of the M as given in the TT, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraY Ald~ama","text_ar":"تَرَى الدَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurY Aldm","text_ar":"يُرى الدم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yaEiy$aA","text_ar":"اَنْ يَعِيشَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", it has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aw yEy$A","text_ar":"او يعيشا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the right reading of the first hemistich seems to be,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDarobK tuxaf~itu faw~aArapK","text_ar":"بِضَرْبٍ تُخَفِّتُ فَوَّارَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for an inf. n. is sometimes made fem.: see an instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darob","text_ar":"ضَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"as fem. in the EM p. 157: the poet means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With a smiting that silences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kills, inflicting a wide and gushing wound; and a piercing"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the spear"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which thou seest the blood sprinkled: when they slay a horseman of you, we are responsible for him after it that he shall live:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., as is said in the M, his blood shall be revenged, so that he will be as though he had not been slain: and it is also there said that by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yxf~t fw~Arh","text_ar":"يخفّت فوّاره"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lnhA wAsEp fdmhA","text_ar":"لنها واسعة فدمها"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ysyl wlA Swt lh","text_ar":"يسيل ولا صوت له"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which the two fem. pronouns and the fem. epithet all relate to the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darob","text_ar":"ضَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with what I have stated to be in my opinion the right reading of the first hemistich.])"}],"source_refs":["IAar","M","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}